John D. Markley Jr.: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 10:37 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of New Amsterdam Growth Capital LLC



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
John D. Markley Jr.Co-Founder and Managing Partner, New Amsterdam Growth Capital LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 8 Board Members in 8 different organizations across 14 different industries.See Board Relationships51--
Background

		Mr. John D. Markley Jr., also known as Jay, is a Co-Founder of New Amsterdam Growth Capital LLC and serves as its Managing Partner. Mr. Markley has been Managing Director of Bear Creek Capital Management since 2009. He is employed as Director at CCH I, LLC. He was a Venture Partner at Columbia Capital LLC from 1996 to 2009. Mr. Markley has experience in the telecommunications and media industries. Mr. Markley served in a number of capacities at Columbia Capital Corporation, ... including as a Partner, Venture Partner and Portfolio Company Executive. He joined Columbia Capital LLC in 1996 and focused on investments in the wireless and broadband sectors. Mr. Markley was actively involved with Hillcrest Communications, Coriolis Networks, Luna Technologies, Inc., Net Devices, PanGo Networks and Photuris. He was actively involved with Hillcrest Laboratories and Inner Wireless. Mr. Markley served at Altiga Networks, Taqua, Softek Storage Solutions, Ocular Networks, Torrent Networking Technologies and WNP Communications. Prior to joining Columbia Capital, he served as a Policy Advisor of Federal Communications Commission from 1994 to 1996, where he developed U.S. Government wireless communications and spectrum auction policy and assisted in the implementation of the Telecommunications Act of 1996. Mr. Markley served positions in real estate and corporate finance for Kidder Peabody Group Inc. and Kidder, Peabody & Co. in both New York City and Hong Kong. He has been the Chairman of BroadSoft, Inc. since January 1, 2013. Mr. Markley has been a Director of Charter Communications, Inc. and CCH II LLC and CCO Holdings LLC since November 30, 2009. He has been a Director of InterDigital, Inc. since November 3, 2016; CCO Holdings Capital Corp., since December 2009 and BroadSoft, Inc., since January 2002. He serves as a Director of egisto Systems, Softek Storage Solutions and Antares Advanced Test Technologies. He served as Director of CircleBack, Inc. until November 21, 2016 He served as a Director of Millennial Media Inc. from July 2006 to May 29, 2014. He served as a Director of ReefEdge Inc., Kirusa Inc., Intersect Software Corporation, Telecom Transport Management, Inc., and Luna Technologies, Inc. He served as a Director of Megisto Systems, Inc. Mr. Markley has a broad range of senior-level capabilities, including board experience with one of the largest cable operators in America as well as two decades of investment experience in the mobile field. Mr. Markley received his M.B.A. from Harvard Business School and B.A. in Economics from Washington and Lee University.Read Full Background




